1
00:00:00,240 --> 00:00:01,640
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,640 --> 00:00:02,810
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:02,810 --> 00:00:05,140
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:06,410 --> 00:00:07,650
The Temi Bio files?

5
00:00:09,210 --> 00:00:10,520
Why the sudden interest in them?

6
00:00:11,450 --> 00:00:12,980
There's something
I need to confirm personally.

7
00:00:16,090 --> 00:00:20,230
The film crew asked
why I joined the Adele Group,

8
00:00:21,090 --> 00:00:23,760
and I told them it was because
I'm interested in Temi Bio.

9
00:00:24,660 --> 00:00:26,300
And when it comes to Temi Bio,

10
00:00:26,560 --> 00:00:30,000
I figured you'd be
the best person to ask.

11
00:00:32,340 --> 00:00:34,710
It was a while ago,
so most of it is probably gone,

12
00:00:35,010 --> 00:00:36,310
but please find everything you can.

13
00:00:36,710 --> 00:00:39,240
Since this is a personal matter,
I hope you'll be discreet.

14
00:00:39,740 --> 00:00:43,110
President Kim and the chairman,
in particular, must not find out.

15
00:00:44,820 --> 00:00:46,320
Yes, I understand.

16
00:00:54,830 --> 00:00:57,760
Jin Ju, the reason
you had to become Chloe...

17
00:00:59,300 --> 00:01:01,500
If I retrace what you did as Chloe,

18
00:01:03,330 --> 00:01:04,400
I'm sure I'll figure it out.

19
00:01:13,280 --> 00:01:15,750
So Kim Dan Hui really did exist.

20
00:01:28,260 --> 00:01:29,790
What is all this gobbledygook?

21
00:01:31,230 --> 00:01:32,760
I can't make heads or tails of it.

22
00:01:32,930 --> 00:01:36,000
Right, it's in English.
I took a look at it earlier.

23
00:01:36,370 --> 00:01:38,600
It says she had ovarian cancer.

24
00:01:39,700 --> 00:01:43,910
- Ovarian cancer?
- Yes, and she died a long time ago.

25
00:01:44,940 --> 00:01:45,940
She's dead?

26
00:01:46,610 --> 00:01:48,780
Wait, are you saying
Kim Dan Hui is dead?

27
00:01:49,350 --> 00:01:51,720
Yes, if you look at the notes
at the bottom,

28
00:01:52,020 --> 00:01:55,890
the patient stopped going
to post-surgery follow-ups,

29
00:01:56,320 --> 00:01:57,960
and the case was later closed
after a death notice.

30
00:01:59,120 --> 00:02:00,120
What else is there?

31
00:02:00,660 --> 00:02:02,790
What about her personal information?
Why isn't that here?

32
00:02:03,260 --> 00:02:06,970
These are just the surgical records,
not her personal file.

33
00:02:18,110 --> 00:02:19,110
How did it go?

34
00:02:19,380 --> 00:02:21,280
Did you find anything
in Kim Dan Hui's records?

35
00:02:22,310 --> 00:02:24,580
Were you so proud of yourself
when that was all you found?

36
00:02:25,350 --> 00:02:27,520
Why the attitude
when you got to read her files?

37
00:02:27,950 --> 00:02:29,690
It just says
she died of her illness.

38
00:02:30,860 --> 00:02:31,860
She died?

39
00:02:34,330 --> 00:02:35,960
Then what does that mean for us?

40
00:02:36,460 --> 00:02:38,800
We thought
President Kim Myung Hui...

41
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:41,100
was actually Kim Dan Hui
under a new identity.

42
00:02:42,470 --> 00:02:43,870
But if Kim Dan Hui is dead,

43
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:47,740
that means President Kim
is who she says she is.

44
00:02:48,440 --> 00:02:51,210
That means
she's not using a false identity.

45
00:02:51,410 --> 00:02:54,310
See? What did I tell you?

46
00:02:54,510 --> 00:02:56,010
You fell for that con artist's lies,

47
00:02:56,680 --> 00:02:58,280
and I ran around for nothing.

48
00:02:59,420 --> 00:03:00,590
Now that it's come to this,

49
00:03:01,490 --> 00:03:03,050
I have to see for myself.

50
00:03:03,590 --> 00:03:05,320
Are you going to visit
that con artist again?

51
00:03:06,930 --> 00:03:09,630
No, I need to see for myself
if Kim Dan Hui is really dead.

52
00:03:09,990 --> 00:03:11,000
What?

53
00:03:11,860 --> 00:03:12,860
Now what?

54
00:03:13,700 --> 00:03:15,570
You want me to go to the beyond
and ask her?

55
00:03:15,630 --> 00:03:17,270
I don't care how you do it.

56
00:03:18,140 --> 00:03:21,210
Bring me definitive proof
that Kim Dan Hui is actually dead.

57
00:03:21,640 --> 00:03:22,670
I don't get it.

58
00:03:23,440 --> 00:03:26,710
Why are you so obsessed with her?

59
00:03:26,710 --> 00:03:27,950
Like I said, it's a gut feeling.

60
00:03:28,780 --> 00:03:31,980
I know for a fact
that I saw Kim Myung Hui flinch.

61
00:03:38,090 --> 00:03:39,290
Your intuition sucks!

62
00:03:40,560 --> 00:03:42,560
Jung Ran, please.

63
00:03:53,040 --> 00:03:55,410
Does this mean Dan Hui's identity
hasn't been exposed?

64
00:03:57,040 --> 00:03:59,310
It sounds like they're trying
to confirm that she's dead.

65
00:04:03,410 --> 00:04:04,820
From the hospital records,

66
00:04:04,820 --> 00:04:06,990
it seems they only confirmed
that Dan Hui is dead.

67
00:04:07,850 --> 00:04:09,220
That's a relief.

68
00:04:10,120 --> 00:04:11,920
Her social security number
would reveal...

69
00:04:11,920 --> 00:04:13,690
that they share the same birthday,

70
00:04:14,190 --> 00:04:17,300
and they might have discovered
that they're twins.

71
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:19,600
Right.

72
00:04:19,630 --> 00:04:22,070
Anyway, it seems like
we've dodged a bullet for now.

73
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:25,240
Hey, since it's come to this,

74
00:04:25,540 --> 00:04:29,510
why don't we step in and prove
Kim Dan Hui is really dead?

75
00:04:29,870 --> 00:04:30,880
What?

76
00:04:31,540 --> 00:04:33,950
Oh Jung Ran told her driver
to find proof...

77
00:04:33,950 --> 00:04:35,510
that Kim Dan Hui is dead.

78
00:04:35,910 --> 00:04:39,720
So before they find something else
during the search,

79
00:04:40,690 --> 00:04:42,550
we should provide
the proof ourselves...

80
00:04:42,550 --> 00:04:43,990
and end this.

81
00:04:44,090 --> 00:04:46,090
- What kind of proof would that be?
- What?

82
00:04:47,890 --> 00:04:49,330
Well, how about...

83
00:04:50,190 --> 00:04:53,130
we show them the urn
in the columbarium?

84
00:04:53,830 --> 00:04:56,430
Are you kidding me?
You call that a plan?

85
00:04:56,800 --> 00:04:59,800
You'd really send those scumbags
to Myung Hui's resting place?

86
00:05:01,310 --> 00:05:02,340
The columbarium
is out of the question.

87
00:05:02,740 --> 00:05:05,380
The urn shows Myung Hui's
date of death,

88
00:05:05,380 --> 00:05:07,210
and that'll only make them
more suspicious.

89
00:05:07,750 --> 00:05:08,750
It's way too risky.

90
00:05:08,880 --> 00:05:11,620
That's all the more reason
for us to act first.

91
00:05:11,750 --> 00:05:13,890
Look at how those people
found the hospital.

92
00:05:14,220 --> 00:05:15,990
They hire people to investigate,

93
00:05:15,990 --> 00:05:17,760
so they'll find the columbarium
in no time.

94
00:05:17,820 --> 00:05:19,460
Even so, that's just too...

95
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:33,540
Should we...

96
00:05:35,840 --> 00:05:36,840
act first?

97
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:54,560
(Adele)

98
00:05:54,660 --> 00:05:57,200
(Consultant, Chloe Lee)

99
00:05:58,160 --> 00:06:00,300
(Team Leader, Choi Yu Na)

100
00:06:03,770 --> 00:06:05,300
Why are you working so hard?

101
00:06:05,900 --> 00:06:07,310
Don't tell me
you're trying to one-up me.

102
00:06:07,970 --> 00:06:09,710
You don't seem
to be doing anything...

103
00:06:09,710 --> 00:06:11,480
or even capable
of doing any research,

104
00:06:11,680 --> 00:06:13,510
so I'm taking matters
into my own hands.

105
00:06:14,050 --> 00:06:17,920
Someone has to figure out
what the world's purest water is.

106
00:06:18,020 --> 00:06:21,120
Are you going to figure it out
and spoon-feed me the answer?

107
00:06:21,390 --> 00:06:24,620
Given our deal,
I'm supposed to help you.

108
00:06:25,260 --> 00:06:26,460
So I suppose I will.

109
00:06:34,930 --> 00:06:35,930
Chloe...

110
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:38,370
Can I really trust her?

111
00:06:45,140 --> 00:06:47,980
Is this that ultrapure water
you were talking about?

112
00:06:48,450 --> 00:06:51,450
Yes, the purest water in the world.

113
00:06:51,780 --> 00:06:53,920
It has virtually no impurities.

114
00:06:55,820 --> 00:06:57,890
Metal ions, microorganisms,

115
00:06:57,960 --> 00:07:01,060
and even all organic matter
have been removed.

116
00:07:01,830 --> 00:07:03,460
It's the best solution...

117
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:05,100
to the mission
Producer Shin gave us.

118
00:07:06,030 --> 00:07:09,570
But this can't be easy to obtain.

119
00:07:09,970 --> 00:07:14,010
Exactly. It's for semiconductors
and precision experiments,

120
00:07:14,070 --> 00:07:16,370
so it's impossible to produce
without the right equipment.

121
00:07:18,140 --> 00:07:21,350
Here. I think this is our best bet.

122
00:07:22,410 --> 00:07:25,450
CX Lab Chemical Research Institute?

123
00:07:25,980 --> 00:07:28,090
They make ultrapure water there,

124
00:07:28,090 --> 00:07:30,250
so we can probably get
a small amount.

125
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:33,960
We're on a tight schedule,
so please go check it out.

126
00:07:34,460 --> 00:07:36,930
Okay. Don't worry.

127
00:07:51,910 --> 00:07:53,140
Ultrapure water?

128
00:07:54,210 --> 00:07:56,880
She's planning to get it
from an outside lab?

129
00:07:58,720 --> 00:08:01,620
But she never said
she'd hand it over after getting it.

130
00:08:03,690 --> 00:08:04,690
Right.

131
00:08:05,320 --> 00:08:07,330
I can't rely solely on Chloe.

132
00:08:14,670 --> 00:08:15,730
Where is Manager So?

133
00:08:16,070 --> 00:08:17,770
He said he had something urgent
to attend to.

134
00:08:18,170 --> 00:08:20,140
Useless, as always.

135
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:22,310
He has no idea
what's actually urgent.

136
00:08:22,510 --> 00:08:23,740
Is something wrong?

137
00:08:26,110 --> 00:08:29,110
Ms. Heo, I need you to go
to Adele Bio's research lab.

138
00:08:30,210 --> 00:08:33,250
Ask if they can make ultrapure water
within two days.

139
00:08:33,720 --> 00:08:34,720
On second thought,

140
00:08:35,290 --> 00:08:37,090
tell them they must.

141
00:08:37,090 --> 00:08:38,390
Out of the blue?

142
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:41,090
But we've never worked
with the research lab before...

143
00:08:41,090 --> 00:08:42,760
What does that have to do
with anything?

144
00:08:44,230 --> 00:08:47,900
I'm Choi Yu Na, and I'll soon
be marrying into the Adele Group.

145
00:08:49,030 --> 00:08:50,740
But that isn't the case yet.

146
00:08:55,740 --> 00:08:58,740
The bio division is
under Director Park Min Jun,

147
00:08:59,140 --> 00:09:01,350
so drop his name if you have to.

148
00:09:01,850 --> 00:09:03,810
Just tell them
to make it immediately.

149
00:09:04,950 --> 00:09:06,080
(Merger and Acquisition
Review Documents)

150
00:09:10,090 --> 00:09:13,060
Is this everything you have
on Temi Bio?

151
00:09:13,320 --> 00:09:16,030
Yes, sir.
This is all the information...

152
00:09:16,360 --> 00:09:17,360
I could gather.

153
00:09:20,560 --> 00:09:23,670
This simply indicates that
there were no issues with the M and A.

154
00:09:27,510 --> 00:09:30,840
Is there anything about the accident
involving Temi Bio CEO Baek Jun Gi?

155
00:09:31,140 --> 00:09:33,610
Those files would be
with the police.

156
00:09:34,910 --> 00:09:38,080
Besides, the accident report
isn't relevant to the business deal.

157
00:09:39,250 --> 00:09:41,520
Understood. You may leave.

158
00:09:42,120 --> 00:09:43,120
Yes, sir.

159
00:09:53,760 --> 00:09:54,830
(Car Plunges off Cliff)

160
00:09:54,830 --> 00:09:55,870
(Temi Bio CEO Baek Jun Gi
and Daughter Found Dead)

161
00:09:58,100 --> 00:10:00,640
There's nothing more I can learn
at the company.

162
00:10:06,010 --> 00:10:08,150
(New Business Task Force Team)

163
00:10:09,650 --> 00:10:14,050
If Jin Ju is alive, does that mean
it wasn't a murder-suicide?

164
00:10:14,390 --> 00:10:15,450
Or...

165
00:10:16,320 --> 00:10:19,260
was she the only one
who survived the crash?

166
00:10:32,900 --> 00:10:34,870
Leaving already?

167
00:10:35,670 --> 00:10:37,710
Yes, I have a personal matter
to attend to.

168
00:10:38,980 --> 00:10:39,980
Excuse me.

169
00:10:57,860 --> 00:10:59,400
(Criminal Division)

170
00:10:59,460 --> 00:11:02,700
Accident records can only be viewed
by an interested party.

171
00:11:03,100 --> 00:11:04,770
Either get the family's
power of attorney...

172
00:11:04,770 --> 00:11:07,240
or have a lawyer request
the information.

173
00:11:12,710 --> 00:11:15,510
So there's nothing I can do
if I'm not family?

174
00:11:17,210 --> 00:11:19,550
Even seven years ago,

175
00:11:20,890 --> 00:11:23,220
was I just as powerless
to help Jin Ju?

176
00:11:27,290 --> 00:11:29,190
It has to be different this time.

177
00:11:29,990 --> 00:11:31,100
Somehow,

178
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:34,800
I have to find a lead.

179
00:11:50,550 --> 00:11:52,350
Is that what you want from me?

180
00:11:56,590 --> 00:11:57,590
How about it?

181
00:11:58,190 --> 00:11:59,390
Should I undress for you right here?

182
00:11:59,390 --> 00:12:01,030
Or would you rather go
somewhere else?

183
00:12:15,670 --> 00:12:17,210
I've been looking all over for you.

184
00:12:19,010 --> 00:12:20,280
Why were you looking for me?

185
00:12:22,180 --> 00:12:25,750
Why? What, are you still pissed?

186
00:12:27,850 --> 00:12:28,920
Do you want to punch me again?

187
00:12:30,960 --> 00:12:32,190
Jin Ju...

188
00:12:37,130 --> 00:12:38,560
Didn't I make myself clear?

189
00:12:39,760 --> 00:12:43,330
To me, she's Chloe, not Baek Jin Ju.
Chloe chose me,

190
00:12:45,240 --> 00:12:46,840
and we're getting married.

191
00:12:48,410 --> 00:12:49,610
Is that all you can think about?

192
00:12:49,610 --> 00:12:52,040
That's all we have to talk about!

193
00:12:56,350 --> 00:12:58,820
How did you know Chloe was Jin Ju?

194
00:13:00,320 --> 00:13:02,420
Did you even bother to find out
why or how...

195
00:13:02,690 --> 00:13:04,390
Jin Ju came back as Chloe,

196
00:13:04,990 --> 00:13:08,560
or what she's trying to do as Chloe
instead of herself?

197
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:19,000
No.

198
00:13:20,970 --> 00:13:22,270
Why does any of that matter?

199
00:13:22,470 --> 00:13:23,570
Any of that?

200
00:13:30,180 --> 00:13:34,650
All you've ever cared about
are your own selfish desires.

201
00:13:35,590 --> 00:13:37,220
Because you wanted her to be Chloe,

202
00:13:37,220 --> 00:13:39,460
you didn't care
what happened to Jin Ju,

203
00:13:40,560 --> 00:13:41,690
so you never bothered to look...

204
00:13:41,690 --> 00:13:42,790
into the incident
from seven years ago.

205
00:13:45,160 --> 00:13:47,800
If that's your idea of love,

206
00:13:49,730 --> 00:13:51,170
isn't that just pathetic?

207
00:13:55,110 --> 00:13:56,170
Hey.

208
00:13:58,880 --> 00:14:00,540
I've had enough of this from you.

209
00:14:02,110 --> 00:14:04,420
Don't you dare act superior
around me again.

210
00:14:10,890 --> 00:14:12,190
How are you any different?

211
00:14:15,030 --> 00:14:18,830
Aren't you digging up her past
because you want her back as Jin Ju?

212
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:20,000
That's right.

213
00:14:23,070 --> 00:14:26,840
I'm looking into the past
to get Jin Ju back.

214
00:14:30,670 --> 00:14:31,680
But,

215
00:14:32,280 --> 00:14:34,350
the more I look back
and investigate,

216
00:14:34,480 --> 00:14:37,450
the more I realize
I knew nothing at all.

217
00:14:37,850 --> 00:14:40,180
I feel guilty
for still not realizing...

218
00:14:40,580 --> 00:14:42,520
how much she was hurting or why.

219
00:14:44,460 --> 00:14:46,420
Those questions you ignored...

220
00:14:46,420 --> 00:14:49,190
might be
an uncomfortable truth you avoid,

221
00:14:51,330 --> 00:14:53,900
but to me,
they're an apology and regret...

222
00:14:53,900 --> 00:14:54,900
that came seven years too late,

223
00:14:56,970 --> 00:14:58,200
and they're also my responsibility.

224
00:15:08,310 --> 00:15:09,410
Darn it!

225
00:15:15,850 --> 00:15:17,020
Get going, already!

226
00:15:17,490 --> 00:15:19,960
I told you to look
into columbariums right now.

227
00:15:20,220 --> 00:15:23,930
Look, I've got people on it.
Just be patient, will you?

228
00:15:23,990 --> 00:15:26,460
That doesn't mean
you can sit around doing nothing.

229
00:15:26,660 --> 00:15:30,070
To get answers faster,
you should be out searching too.

230
00:15:30,070 --> 00:15:31,600
What's the big rush?

231
00:15:32,100 --> 00:15:34,640
We'll hear back from them
soon enough.

232
00:15:35,140 --> 00:15:37,710
When? When will they get back to us?

233
00:15:37,780 --> 00:15:40,640
- When?
- Can you just...

234
00:15:43,750 --> 00:15:46,280
See? We just got word.

235
00:15:52,490 --> 00:15:56,160
(The late Kim Dan Hui,
died November 2, 1998)

236
00:15:56,430 --> 00:15:59,200
So, Kim Dan Hui is really dead?

237
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:02,930
Looks like hiring all those people
and spending that money paid off.

238
00:16:03,870 --> 00:16:05,900
You got your confirmation,
so just drop it.

239
00:16:06,600 --> 00:16:07,640
Wait a second.

240
00:16:10,010 --> 00:16:11,480
(The late Kim Dan Hui,
died November 2, 1998)

241
00:16:11,580 --> 00:16:13,510
Kim Myung Hui barged into our house,

242
00:16:14,650 --> 00:16:16,680
and Kim Dan Hui died
a long time after that.

243
00:16:17,450 --> 00:16:20,250
See? I told you so.

244
00:16:21,020 --> 00:16:23,020
This is so frustrating.

245
00:16:23,620 --> 00:16:26,160
What are we supposed to do
if she's actually dead?

246
00:16:26,760 --> 00:16:29,590
A waste of time and money.
What was this whole circus for?

247
00:16:29,660 --> 00:16:31,060
Who's to blame?

248
00:16:31,430 --> 00:16:33,500
It's your own fault for falling
for that con artist's lies.

249
00:16:34,300 --> 00:16:36,200
The one who tricked me is to blame.

250
00:16:37,570 --> 00:16:40,800
You make sure that prat
never gets out.

251
00:16:40,870 --> 00:16:42,010
Bury him in petitions.

252
00:16:42,410 --> 00:16:45,640
Write a hundred,
no, make it a thousand!

253
00:16:45,940 --> 00:16:46,980
Darn it.

254
00:16:50,880 --> 00:16:52,020
You and your lousy intuition.

255
00:16:52,920 --> 00:16:54,050
Wait up.

256
00:17:02,130 --> 00:17:04,400
I guess they had a lot of people
looking into it.

257
00:17:05,630 --> 00:17:08,100
They didn't even question
the text we sent.

258
00:17:14,170 --> 00:17:16,870
Good thing we changed the date
on the urn beforehand.

259
00:17:24,420 --> 00:17:28,090
(The late Kim Dan Hui)

260
00:17:28,150 --> 00:17:30,890
(The late Kim Dan Hui,
died October 7, 1997)

261
00:17:31,690 --> 00:17:32,690
Myung Hui.

262
00:17:35,130 --> 00:17:36,260
I'm sorry.

263
00:17:36,990 --> 00:17:39,200
I haven't been able
to do anything for you yet.

264
00:17:41,930 --> 00:17:43,270
I felt so guilty,

265
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:45,700
so terribly guilty,

266
00:17:47,670 --> 00:17:49,510
that I couldn't even bring myself
to visit.

267
00:17:53,210 --> 00:17:55,050
But I brought those people
before you.

268
00:17:57,950 --> 00:18:01,820
I made you look at the ones
who killed you.

269
00:18:06,390 --> 00:18:07,560
I'm sorry.

270
00:18:11,260 --> 00:18:13,400
I've done nothing to make you proud,

271
00:18:15,600 --> 00:18:16,670
and I'm sorry.

272
00:18:18,270 --> 00:18:19,670
I'm so sorry.

273
00:18:27,480 --> 00:18:28,510
It's okay.

274
00:18:29,580 --> 00:18:32,020
Myung Hui would've understood.

275
00:18:34,280 --> 00:18:37,390
She'd have been so happy to see you,
even like this.

276
00:18:39,390 --> 00:18:42,830
And she'd be relieved
you got Oh Jung Ran off your trail.

277
00:18:44,190 --> 00:18:45,430
That's what she'd say.

278
00:18:49,070 --> 00:18:50,470
Now, it's my turn.

279
00:18:51,700 --> 00:18:54,040
Since Oh Jung Ran has been digging
into my past,

280
00:18:56,110 --> 00:18:59,640
I'll use her own past
to get back at her.

281
00:19:09,950 --> 00:19:12,720
You want to know
about Ms. Oh Jung Ran?

282
00:19:13,660 --> 00:19:14,660
Yes.

283
00:19:15,360 --> 00:19:18,700
Specifically,
I want to know about her past.

284
00:19:21,870 --> 00:19:25,540
Last time, it was
Chairman Park Tae Ho of Adele,

285
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:30,440
and now you're asking me
to look into his wife's past.

286
00:19:31,840 --> 00:19:36,050
You don't seem the type to do this
over a simple family squabble.

287
00:19:36,550 --> 00:19:38,820
May I ask why?

288
00:19:39,120 --> 00:19:40,450
Knowing Oh Jung Ran,

289
00:19:40,780 --> 00:19:43,490
her past must be full
of wicked deeds.

290
00:19:44,520 --> 00:19:45,520
Until now,

291
00:19:46,090 --> 00:19:49,160
I've looked the other way,
thinking she'd never be punished.

292
00:19:49,930 --> 00:19:53,800
But now I've changed my mind.
I think I can punish her myself,

293
00:19:54,400 --> 00:19:55,870
outside the law.

294
00:19:56,370 --> 00:20:00,440
Chairman Park Tae Ho of Adele,
and his wife, Oh Jung Ran.

295
00:20:01,340 --> 00:20:04,610
You intend to take on both of them?

296
00:20:08,550 --> 00:20:11,450
Yes. Can you help me?

297
00:20:11,950 --> 00:20:15,350
To be honest, I need your help.

298
00:20:19,020 --> 00:20:21,120
Oh Jung Ran's past,

299
00:20:22,830 --> 00:20:24,490
including any misdeeds.

300
00:20:25,060 --> 00:20:26,660
I'll look into it.

301
00:20:41,810 --> 00:20:42,810
Yes, hello?

302
00:20:44,880 --> 00:20:47,820
Wait, the CX Lab?

303
00:20:52,020 --> 00:20:54,190
You wanted ultrapure water, right?

304
00:20:54,390 --> 00:20:56,390
We've reviewed your request,
and we can deliver.

305
00:20:56,490 --> 00:20:58,660
You'll just need to come in
and fill out some paperwork.

306
00:20:58,900 --> 00:21:01,430
I see. Can I come over right now?

307
00:21:03,130 --> 00:21:04,430
Yes, I understand.

308
00:21:07,770 --> 00:21:11,040
Can I really count on you
for this extra mission?

309
00:21:12,110 --> 00:21:14,210
Just wait and see.

310
00:21:24,020 --> 00:21:25,360
Even now,

311
00:21:25,920 --> 00:21:28,230
you're not telling me anything
about the ultrapure water.

312
00:21:30,190 --> 00:21:33,360
I knew it wasn't wise
to rely on her alone.

313
00:21:36,170 --> 00:21:38,770
The bio research lab really needs
to come through for me.

314
00:21:47,110 --> 00:21:48,110
What's wrong?

315
00:21:49,210 --> 00:21:50,750
Did the lab refuse?

316
00:21:50,810 --> 00:21:53,150
Without an order
from the president or the director,

317
00:21:53,350 --> 00:21:55,790
they said they couldn't produce it
for personal use.

318
00:21:55,850 --> 00:21:58,120
Then you should've just lied!

319
00:22:00,960 --> 00:22:04,630
I'm running out of time.
Where do I get ultrapure water now?

320
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:10,670
(Consultant, Chloe Lee)

321
00:22:22,980 --> 00:22:26,350
That's all for the paperwork.
You can pick it up when it's ready.

322
00:22:26,450 --> 00:22:30,020
When do you think it'll be ready?
I'm on a bit of a tight schedule.

323
00:22:30,090 --> 00:22:33,890
The equipment is currently occupied
with another process.

324
00:22:34,260 --> 00:22:37,990
It'll be ready by 6 p.m. tomorrow.
Would that work for you?

325
00:22:38,060 --> 00:22:39,900
Yes. That's fine.

326
00:22:40,160 --> 00:22:41,770
I'll see you tomorrow then.

327
00:22:41,770 --> 00:22:43,330
Sure. Take care.

328
00:22:50,910 --> 00:22:52,340
Hello?

329
00:22:53,010 --> 00:22:54,880
Yes. You mean Chloe?

330
00:22:56,010 --> 00:22:57,580
She just stepped out.

331
00:22:58,720 --> 00:23:00,180
Oh, the ultrapure water?

332
00:23:00,680 --> 00:23:03,420
It'll be ready for pickup tomorrow
at 6 p.m.

333
00:23:04,090 --> 00:23:05,090
Sure.

334
00:23:09,930 --> 00:23:11,630
Tomorrow at 6 p.m.?

335
00:23:16,430 --> 00:23:17,870
Kim Dan Hui...

336
00:23:18,600 --> 00:23:21,610
She was definitely rattled
when she heard that name.

337
00:23:22,140 --> 00:23:25,180
Come on.
Kim Dan Hui is dead, isn't she?

338
00:23:25,240 --> 00:23:26,580
You saw it with your own eyes.

339
00:23:27,380 --> 00:23:29,250
Kim Myung Hui, Kim Dan Hui.

340
00:23:30,010 --> 00:23:31,780
Their names are similar.
Could they be related?

341
00:23:32,680 --> 00:23:35,650
Wait a minute.
Kim Dan Hui was adopted too, right?

342
00:23:35,750 --> 00:23:39,160
Even if two people had similar names
and were both orphans,

343
00:23:39,260 --> 00:23:42,530
what does that have to do
with her faking her identity?

344
00:23:42,590 --> 00:23:44,760
Gosh, this is so complicated.

345
00:23:45,060 --> 00:23:47,500
Something about this
just doesn't sit right with me.

346
00:23:47,800 --> 00:23:48,900
Ms. Oh.

347
00:23:54,200 --> 00:23:55,270
What?

348
00:23:55,870 --> 00:23:57,670
Ms. Choi, what brings you here?

349
00:23:58,410 --> 00:24:00,340
I've come to ask you for a favor.

350
00:24:02,080 --> 00:24:04,610
A favor from me?

351
00:24:06,250 --> 00:24:10,120
No matter how I see it,
you and I have the same goal.

352
00:24:10,920 --> 00:24:13,590
Don't you want me
to win this competition?

353
00:24:15,560 --> 00:24:20,000
Help me beat Chloe
in the extra mission.

354
00:24:23,900 --> 00:24:24,900
The nerve.

355
00:24:24,900 --> 00:24:27,140
Hold on. What are you doing?

356
00:24:27,200 --> 00:24:28,940
Who are you trying
to stand in the way of?

357
00:24:29,410 --> 00:24:32,780
If you win,
our Hyun Jun can't marry Chloe.

358
00:24:34,080 --> 00:24:35,180
Ms. Oh,

359
00:24:36,350 --> 00:24:38,520
you don't want Chloe
to marry him, do you?

360
00:24:39,520 --> 00:24:41,220
If you help me just this once,

361
00:24:41,380 --> 00:24:44,990
I can remove Chloe from the picture
for good.

362
00:24:48,690 --> 00:24:49,690
Don't listen to her.

363
00:24:50,490 --> 00:24:53,430
You have to think of Hyun Jun
and take his side.

364
00:24:54,530 --> 00:24:55,900
Do you want to see him hurt again?

365
00:24:55,900 --> 00:24:57,870
You should stay out of this,
old man.

366
00:24:59,300 --> 00:25:02,440
Who are you calling old?
Do I look like an old man to you?

367
00:25:04,410 --> 00:25:05,410
Darn.

368
00:25:06,180 --> 00:25:08,210
- Darn it.
- What?

369
00:25:10,050 --> 00:25:12,780
Hey. That's enough, both of you.

370
00:25:15,420 --> 00:25:18,460
So what kind of help do you need?

371
00:25:19,060 --> 00:25:20,520
Jung Ran, please!

372
00:25:22,730 --> 00:25:26,530
After all the trouble I went through
to find Kim Myung Hui's weakness,

373
00:25:26,860 --> 00:25:28,900
you expect me to do nothing
about Hyun Jun's marriage?

374
00:25:29,570 --> 00:25:32,370
Don't I get to have things
go my way for once?

375
00:25:32,470 --> 00:25:35,770
You should be thinking
about Hyun Jun, not yourself...

376
00:25:35,770 --> 00:25:36,840
Quiet.

377
00:25:37,170 --> 00:25:38,880
You better keep your mouth shut.

378
00:25:39,410 --> 00:25:41,480
If you go running your mouth
to Hyun Jun again,

379
00:25:42,180 --> 00:25:43,910
I swear
I'll cut you out of my life...

380
00:25:44,750 --> 00:25:46,120
for good.

381
00:25:53,990 --> 00:25:55,630
(Adele)

382
00:25:55,790 --> 00:25:58,190
(Chairman Park Tae Ho)

383
00:25:58,190 --> 00:26:01,160
You told me to sell two paintings,
and I've chosen these.

384
00:26:01,530 --> 00:26:04,770
I'll sell them to raise funds
for the deal.

385
00:26:06,500 --> 00:26:08,670
Sure. Go ahead.

386
00:26:10,870 --> 00:26:12,740
And how's my wife handling this?

387
00:26:13,540 --> 00:26:14,540
I'm not sure.

388
00:26:14,810 --> 00:26:18,180
She must be distracted by something,
since she isn't paying attention.

389
00:26:18,420 --> 00:26:19,550
Unbelievable.

390
00:26:20,350 --> 00:26:23,620
Always distracted by useless things.

391
00:26:25,290 --> 00:26:27,320
And about tomorrow...

392
00:26:28,490 --> 00:26:30,590
I mean, the extra mission
for Ms. Choi and Chloe.

393
00:26:31,160 --> 00:26:32,330
The extra mission?

394
00:26:33,700 --> 00:26:34,730
Didn't you know?

395
00:26:35,600 --> 00:26:38,230
Were you too distracted
to keep up with things?

396
00:26:40,100 --> 00:26:41,100
I apologize.

397
00:26:41,870 --> 00:26:44,640
I was so focused on the gallery,
I must've missed it.

398
00:26:46,740 --> 00:26:50,310
Anyway, be there
for the mission presentation tomorrow.

399
00:26:51,150 --> 00:26:52,150
Got it?

400
00:26:53,520 --> 00:26:56,290
One of the two, Ms. Choi or Chloe,

401
00:26:57,890 --> 00:26:58,990
is definitely...

402
00:26:59,520 --> 00:27:00,590
getting cut.

403
00:27:02,190 --> 00:27:03,190
Yes, sir.

404
00:27:11,500 --> 00:27:14,570
(Consultant, Chloe Lee)

405
00:27:25,950 --> 00:27:27,020
What do you want?

406
00:27:30,090 --> 00:27:32,290
I heard they added an extra mission
to the competition.

407
00:27:34,490 --> 00:27:37,030
I'll handle it myself,
so don't worry about it.

408
00:27:40,360 --> 00:27:41,360
The competition...

409
00:27:44,400 --> 00:27:45,400
Are you still going through with it?

410
00:27:49,870 --> 00:27:51,710
Are you still going ahead with this,

411
00:27:54,110 --> 00:27:55,310
even if it leads to our marriage?

412
00:27:59,150 --> 00:28:00,220
For now, yes.

413
00:28:02,020 --> 00:28:04,620
I'd rather not lose my job.

414
00:28:15,100 --> 00:28:16,200
What are you doing here?

415
00:28:19,070 --> 00:28:20,800
I came to have a word with Chloe.

416
00:28:21,100 --> 00:28:23,240
About what?
Whatever it is, say it to me.

417
00:28:23,310 --> 00:28:24,510
What good will that do?

418
00:28:25,140 --> 00:28:27,710
You think you know
what that thing is really up to?

419
00:28:27,910 --> 00:28:30,910
Do you know her real motive
for marrying you?

420
00:28:33,450 --> 00:28:35,520
All right, I get it.
Just go. Please.

421
00:28:40,090 --> 00:28:42,630
You. What are you really after?

422
00:28:43,490 --> 00:28:45,500
I mean, you...

423
00:28:46,130 --> 00:28:47,900
You don't really care about my son,
do you?

424
00:28:48,900 --> 00:28:51,900
You're just a gold digger
looking for a payday.

425
00:28:53,140 --> 00:28:57,640
That's not happening on my watch.
Got it?

426
00:28:59,110 --> 00:29:01,680
Yes, I hear you loud and clear.

427
00:29:02,280 --> 00:29:04,850
I'm afraid I'm short on time today,
so we'll have to stop here.

428
00:29:05,010 --> 00:29:06,350
We can pick this up again next time.

429
00:29:06,980 --> 00:29:08,350
Now, if you'll excuse me.

430
00:29:13,060 --> 00:29:14,160
Where do you think you're going?

431
00:29:14,520 --> 00:29:17,230
Watch your manners
when I'm talking to you.

432
00:29:17,530 --> 00:29:19,900
Did your parents raise you
to behave like this?

433
00:29:24,630 --> 00:29:25,640
Seriously?

434
00:29:26,040 --> 00:29:28,910
How dare you glare at me like that?

435
00:29:29,370 --> 00:29:30,540
Mom!

436
00:29:31,270 --> 00:29:33,580
Mom, please. Stop.

437
00:29:35,080 --> 00:29:36,180
That's enough!

438
00:29:37,980 --> 00:29:39,980
Who do you think you're shouting at?

439
00:29:40,780 --> 00:29:43,550
Don't you ever
treat Chloe like that again.

440
00:29:44,250 --> 00:29:45,860
What did you just say?

441
00:29:49,130 --> 00:29:50,290
Is this the kind of man you are?

442
00:29:50,890 --> 00:29:53,160
How could you let Chloe
be treated this way?

443
00:30:01,870 --> 00:30:03,310
What do you think you're doing?

444
00:30:04,370 --> 00:30:07,780
Who do you think
you're lecturing right now?

445
00:30:08,610 --> 00:30:09,610
Mom!

446
00:30:18,890 --> 00:30:19,890
That's enough.

447
00:30:47,180 --> 00:30:49,450
(Authorized personnel only,
Do not touch)

448
00:30:51,120 --> 00:30:53,120
(Authorized personnel only,
Do not touch)

449
00:30:58,630 --> 00:31:00,500
So this is the ultrapure water.

450
00:31:04,970 --> 00:31:06,570
I've basically won
this extra mission.

451
00:31:08,710 --> 00:31:09,710
Who are you?

452
00:31:41,440 --> 00:31:44,270
(Pearl in Red)

453
00:31:44,470 --> 00:31:47,010
Police. We're here for Choi Yu Na.

454
00:31:47,010 --> 00:31:48,980
- Sir!
- It'll all go as planned, right?

455
00:31:49,180 --> 00:31:52,150
Yes, sir. Once the investigation
officially begins,

456
00:31:52,720 --> 00:31:55,520
Choi Yu Na will be framed
as the culprit.

457
00:31:55,550 --> 00:31:58,320
She'll face criminal charges
and a civil suit for damages.

458
00:31:58,520 --> 00:31:59,520
The whole situation will escalate.

459
00:31:59,520 --> 00:32:02,090
Looks like everything's
falling into place.

460
00:32:02,230 --> 00:32:04,730
You don't love her,
you just want to own her?

461
00:32:05,060 --> 00:32:07,000
I guess that's my kind of love.

462
00:32:07,360 --> 00:32:11,200
Help me get Chloe,
and I'll help you get...

463
00:32:11,330 --> 00:32:12,770
what you want in return.

464
00:32:13,600 --> 00:32:15,610
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
